<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-07-11T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-07-11T12:00:00-05:00" n="526" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d526">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.12155/436: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morrow</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-07-11T13:00:00-04:00">July 11, 1930—1
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>176. Your 140, July 9 noon. You are authorized to initiate negotiations
                            with Mexican Government relative to Rio Grande River rectification
                            project when you consider the moment propitious. Department is hopeful
                            that an agreement may be reached which will include a final settlement
                            of Chamizal and other territorial differences existing between the two
                            countries in the region covered by the rectification project.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
